Streaming replication with slot
step1:- check the primary server status if the postgres is running it if.
step2:- switch to postgres user | su - postgres
step3:- change the configration file parameters from  => vi /var /lib/pgsql/17/data/postgresql.conf
1. wal_level = 'replica'  -> replica is only for streaming replication
2. max_wal_sender = 10(by default)
3. max_replicat ion_slots = 10(default) 
4. wal_keep_size = 512MB
step4:- add standby ip in hba.conf file
LOCAL    DATABASE         USER            ADDRESS     METHOD
host  replication role_of_replication_user  ip_a     scram-sha-256
step5 :- after changees must restart the service of postgresql
-> if we change from postgresql.conf|postgresql.auto.conf for this only restart the service and any changes from pg_hba.conf then relaod the service from root user oor connect to database and select pg_reload_conf();
step6 :- to create user for replication 
create role rolename with replication login passwor 'password';
if we want add some superuser, adduser, ... by using alter query :- alter role rolename with superuser 

this the option we can create while running the basebackup -C -S <slotname>
// step7:- connect the database for create a slot 
to create slot query :- select pg_create_physical_replication_slot('slot_name');   
to check the slot :- select * from pg_replication_Slots;
to drop the slot :- select pg_drop_repliaction_slot('slot_name') //

step8 :- to check the slot is create or not 
select * from pg_repliaction_slots;
step9 :- from standby server just stop the service 
step10 :- take backup and remove the data file from standby server
step11 :- take basebackup from primary server
pg_basebackup -U roleUser -h ip/localhost -p port -D data_directory_of_standby -P -R -Xs -c fast -v -C -s slotname 
Example:-  pg_basebackup -U replicator -h 192.248.156.245 -p 5432 -D /var/lib/pgsql/17/data/ -P -R -Xs -c fast -v -C -s sr_slot
-u username of role to create from create user 
-h hostname/ip address => 192.168.1.10 (primary)
-p port (optional) => primary port(5432)
-D data directory (standy data directory)
-Fp formate plain (optional)
-Xs :- it means streaming backup method (wal method)
-R write-recovery-conf file/ it create standby.signalfile in PostgreSQL.auto.conf and it add primary host entry (automtically creates standby.singnal connection in auto.conf)
-c fast :- fast check point
-C create slots -S solt_name
-v verbose
-P progress(backup progress)/ show progress information
